The paper discusses a method for treating missing entries in pairwise comparisons, which is a common technique used in decision-making and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves numerical experiments, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.LG (machine learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the quality of data, which may fall under cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science).
